The paper deals with the study of dynamic networks and time-varying graphs, which are fundamental concepts in distributed computing. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.DS (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). The paper also discusses the use of formal models and techniques to study network properties, which falls under the scope of cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Additionally, the paper deals with the evolution of network properties, which is related to cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also discusses the use of TVGs to study the behavior of complex systems, which is related to cs.SY (Systems and Control). Finally, the paper briefly discusses the introduction of randomness in TVGs, which is related to cs.SD (Software Engineering).
